                      Without a clear strategy, marketing often breaks down into
                      fragmented activities. Companies invest in campaigns, but
                      without measurement and direction, efficiency is lost.
                      Meanwhile, competitors are targeting precisely and
                      strengthening their position. A marketing strategy ensures
                      consistency, data-driven decisions, and alignment of all
                      actions toward growth.
                    </p>
